The deal was this far,
no further.

91
00:10:04.354 --> 00:10:07.065
The deal is the deal.
Rule number one.

92
00:10:07.148 --> 00:10:09.651
- Rules are meant to be broken.
- Not mine.

93
00:10:12.821 --> 00:10:16.282
Let's go.
Get in the car.

94
00:10:16.366 --> 00:10:18.243
<i>Come on! Hurry!</i>

95
00:10:19.327 --> 00:10:22.372
- Move it!
<i>- [Engine Starts]</i>

96
00:10:46.771 --> 00:10:49.065
<i>[Birds Chirping]</i>

97
00:10:56.156 --> 00:10:58.741
<i>[Seagull Squawking]</i>

98
00:11:01.369 --> 00:11:03.454
<i>[TV: Man, Indistinct]</i>

99
00:11:03.538 --> 00:11:05.456
<i>[Man #1 On TV]
Really. I did.</i>

100
00:11:05.540 --> 00:11:08.585
<i>[Man #2] Oh, yeah. Well, how come
you don't have your yeﬂow card with you?</i>

101
00:11:08.668 --> 00:11:11.880
<i>[Man #1] Well, l- I must have left it
back in 'Nam on the base.</i>

102
00:11:11.963 --> 00:11:15.008
<i>[Man #2] They all say that.
Left it back in 'Nam on the base. Uh-huh.</i>

103
00:11:15.091 --> 00:11:18.428
<i>Let me show you what we do to people
who left it back in 'Nam on the base.</i>

104
00:11:18.511 --> 00:11:20.638
<i>[Man #1] Please let go of me.
Where are you taking me?</i>

105
00:11:20.722 --> 00:11:23.600
<i>[Man #2] You gotta be punished
for not carrying your shot record on you.</i>

106
00:11:23.683 --> 00:11:26.269
<i>- It's a fate far worse than death.
- [Man #1] Oh, help. Help.</i>

107
00:11:26.352 --> 00:11:28.730
<i>What could be
worse than death?</i>

108
00:11:28.813 --> 00:11:30.815
<i>[Continues, Indistinct]</i>

109
00:11:30.899 --> 00:11:34.611
<i>The Argentinean government
reaffirmed its commitment…</i>

110
00:11:34.694 --> 00:11:37.197
to meeting
the I.M.F.'s target this year.

111
00:11:37.280 --> 00:11:41.701
And yesterday, in Nice, four men robbed
the Alliance Investment Corporation.

112
00:11:41.784 --> 00:11:44.162
One man died on the sidewalk.

113
00:11:44.245 --> 00:11:47.207
<i>The others were apprehended
early this morning…</i>

114
00:11:47.290 --> 00:11:52.545
when they took a wrong turn on a one-way
street in Avignon and ran into a taxicab.

115
00:11:52.629 --> 00:11:55.131
<i>The police said were it not
for their poor driving habits…</i>

116
00:11:55.215 --> 00:11:57.300
the 20 million euros
in bearer bonds...

117
00:11:57.383 --> 00:12:01.512
<i>would have been cashed
and gone by this afternoon.</i>

118
00:12:01.596 --> 00:12:03.598
<i>- In other news, the stock market closed-
- [Bell Dings]</i>

119
00:12:04.974 --> 00:12:07.852
<i>I always say the way
a man treats his car…</i>

120
00:12:07.936 --> 00:12:09.854
is how he treats himself.

121
00:12:11.606 --> 00:12:14.734
<i>- I'd say that's probably true, Inspector.</i>
- [Laughs]

122
00:12:14.817 --> 00:12:17.779
You have a good sense of humor
for a foreigner, Monsieur Frank.

123
00:12:17.862 --> 00:12:23.076
Like the French. Sly wit.
Just the right amount of flavor.

124
00:12:23.159 --> 00:12:26.329
- Been out driving?
- Till they pass a law says I can't.

125
00:12:26.412 --> 00:12:28.456
Want to come in
for a coffee?

126
00:12:28.539 --> 00:12:31.251
Uh, thank you, but I have
a lot of stops to make.

127
00:12:31.334 --> 00:12:33.253
Eighty-eight to be exact.

128
00:12:33.336 --> 00:12:35.838
That's a lot of stops.

129
00:12:35.922 --> 00:12:40.218
A lot of 1999
black BMW 765s…

130
00:12:40.301 --> 00:12:43.763
with 06 in the license plates
to check out.

131
00:12:43.846 --> 00:12:47.475
Ah, it's a very popular car
with a certain type down here.

132
00:12:47.558 --> 00:12:52.272
You've seen them. They come over
from Italy in those very expensive suits...

133
00:12:52.355 --> 00:12:56.234
and the young pretty girls with the big jewelry
and too much makeup.

134
00:12:56.317 --> 00:12:59.320
Very... maﬁa.

135
00:12:59.404 --> 00:13:02.365
There was a robbery.
A getaway.

136
00:13:02.448 --> 00:13:06.119
Some very fancy driving.

137
00:13:06.202 --> 00:13:10.665
By someone in a 1999
black BMW 735?

138
00:13:10.748 --> 00:13:13.293
- With 06 in the plate.
- [Chuckles]

139
00:13:13.376 --> 00:13:16.087
[Chuckles]
You have been to the city lately?

140
00:13:16.170 --> 00:13:18.089
Not for a while.

141
00:13:18.172 --> 00:13:22.510
I love Nice. The food.
The way they grill ﬁsh.

142
00:13:22.593 --> 00:13:25.805
<i>No place else in France
does it the way they do in Nice.</i>

143
00:13:25.888 --> 00:13:27.849
And the women-

144
00:13:27.932 --> 00:13:30.685
I prefer the women there.

145
00:13:30.768 --> 00:13:33.062
They are more... complicated...

146
00:13:34.605 --> 00:13:36.816
than the local variety.

147
00:13:36.899 --> 00:13:38.818
Don't you think?

148
00:13:39.902 --> 00:13:42.405
I don't particularly
like complicated.

149
00:13:42.488 --> 00:13:45.616
- You like to keep it simple.
- Why are you so interested?

150
00:13:45.700 --> 00:13:49.329
Oh, you know, uh,
ever since I'm a little boy...

151
00:13:49.412 --> 00:13:51.539
military people
have always intrigued me.

152
00:13:51.622 --> 00:13:53.458
I'm ex-military.

153
00:13:53.541 --> 00:13:56.419
- I am an ex-little boy.
- [Chuckles]

154
00:14:02.216 --> 00:14:05.386
Sure you don't
have time for a coffee?

155
00:14:05.470 --> 00:14:09.223
Everything is always so neat
with you, Monsieur Frank.

156
00:14:11.309 --> 00:14:15.063
- Nothing ever out of place.
- I'll take that as a compliment...

157
00:14:15.146 --> 00:14:18.608
coming from a man
who pays attention to every detail.

158
00:14:20.401 --> 00:14:24.072
Maybe I'll come back later
for that coffee.

159
00:14:25.615 --> 00:14:28.785
- Door's always open to you.
-Hmm.

160
00:14:30.953 --> 00:14:34.332
[Grunts]

161
00:14:34.457 --> 00:14:37.543
<i>- [Engine Starts]
- [Cell Phone Rings]</i>

162
00:14:39.962 --> 00:14:42.048
- [Man] Lupo gave me your number.
- Be brief.

163
00:14:42.131 --> 00:14:44.759
- I'm looking for a transporter.
- I'm listening.

164
00:14:45.885 --> 00:14:47.970
<i>♪♪ [Stereo: Woman Singing]</i>

165
00:14:50.431 --> 00:14:53.684
- One bag. That's it.
- Dimensions?

166
00:14:55.311 --> 00:14:56.979
Be specific.

167
00:14:57.063 --> 00:14:59.023
One meter 50
by half meter.

168
00:14:59.107 --> 00:15:02.235
- Weight.
- Fifty kilos. Not more.

169
00:15:02.318 --> 00:15:05.571
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

170
00:15:05.655 --> 00:15:08.074
- Destination?
- 24 Rue de Luxembourg.

171
00:15:08.157 --> 00:15:11.994
- You're delivering to Mr.-
- Rule two: No names.

172
00:15:12.078 --> 00:15:14.247
♪♪ [Continues]

173
00:15:14.330 --> 00:15:16.082
