275
00:27:30.315 --> 00:27:32.818
<i>[Motorcycle Engine Revving]</i>

276
00:28:31.126 --> 00:28:33.212
<i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

277
00:28:33.295 --> 00:28:35.297
<i>♪♪ [Hip-hop On Speakers]</i>

278
00:28:35.380 --> 00:28:37.382
[Chuckles]

279
00:28:39.843 --> 00:28:41.803
<i>What the f-</i>

280
00:28:41.887 --> 00:28:43.639
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

281
00:28:51.647 --> 00:28:53.190
[Shouting]

282
00:28:53.273 --> 00:28:54.816
[Shouts]

283
00:29:12.751 --> 00:29:14.503
Where is he?

284
00:29:55.085 --> 00:29:56.169
[Groans]

285
00:30:46.428 --> 00:30:48.055
[Engine Starts]

286
00:30:56.563 --> 00:30:58.148
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

287
00:31:11.703 --> 00:31:13.288
♪♪ [Stops]

288
00:31:40.607 --> 00:31:43.026
You're like dog shit.

289
00:31:43.110 --> 00:31:45.779
You're everywhere. Yeah.

290
00:31:45.862 --> 00:31:48.740
I know you want to pee.
All you want to do is pee.

291
00:31:48.824 --> 00:31:51.034
[Muffled Shouting]

292
00:31:51.118 --> 00:31:55.872
[Muffled Shouting]

293
00:31:57.541 --> 00:31:59.543
Shit.

294
00:32:00.669 --> 00:32:02.504
[Shouting Continues]

295
00:32:05.132 --> 00:32:08.176
[Tires Screech]

296
00:32:08.260 --> 00:32:12.222
<i>♪♪ [R and B]</i>

297
00:32:16.685 --> 00:32:18.728
Frank, you stupid shit.

298
00:32:18.812 --> 00:32:21.690
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

299
00:32:21.773 --> 00:32:24.192
[Screams]

300
00:32:27.737 --> 00:32:31.825
[Screaming]

301
00:32:31.908 --> 00:32:34.161
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

302
00:32:34.244 --> 00:32:35.579
[Screams]

303
00:32:35.662 --> 00:32:37.581
<i>- [Muffled Scream]
- ♪♪ [Ends]</i>

304
00:33:31.551 --> 00:33:33.470
[Sighs]

305
00:33:46.191 --> 00:33:48.777
I ask the questions.
You answer the questions.

306
00:33:48.860 --> 00:33:51.112
No long speeches.
Just keep it simple. Got it?

307
00:33:55.367 --> 00:33:57.369
Who are you?

308
00:33:57.452 --> 00:33:59.454
My name is Lai.
I come from-

309
00:34:01.039 --> 00:34:04.042
I ask the questions.
You answer the questions.

310
00:34:04.125 --> 00:34:07.295
Nothing more, nothing less.
You want to try again?

311
00:34:12.300 --> 00:34:14.928
- What kind of shit am I in?
- Deep shit.

312
00:34:15.011 --> 00:34:17.138
Very deep shit.
Those guys-

313
00:34:17.222 --> 00:34:19.516
- Sorry! Sorry! I won't say any-
<i>- [Bell Dings]</i>

314
00:34:20.725 --> 00:34:22.978
[Sighs]

315
00:34:49.254 --> 00:34:51.172
<i>Bon appétit.</i>

316
00:34:52.173 --> 00:34:54.843
- Where are you going?
- To bed.

317
00:34:54.926 --> 00:34:57.012
<i>Can't think straight
when I'm tired,</i>

318
00:34:57.095 --> 00:34:59.681
A good night's sleep,
I always see things better.

319
00:34:59.764 --> 00:35:02.350
- Can I leave?
- Be my guest.

320
00:35:31.880 --> 00:35:33.840
[Yelps]

321
00:35:36.343 --> 00:35:38.720
[Coughs]

322
00:36:11.044 --> 00:36:13.797
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

323
00:36:47.455 --> 00:36:49.624
<i>[Machine Beeping]</i>

324
00:36:57.215 --> 00:37:00.051
Hey.

325
00:37:00.135 --> 00:37:02.554
Are you comfortable?

326
00:37:02.637 --> 00:37:05.348
- Boss-
- Shh. Save your strength.

327
00:37:05.432 --> 00:37:09.102
Just tell me.
Who did this?

328
00:37:09.185 --> 00:37:11.980
The transporter.

329
00:37:13.022 --> 00:37:14.983
The transporter's dead.

330
00:37:15.066 --> 00:37:17.026
He's not.

331
00:37:22.490 --> 00:37:24.033
Believe me.

332
00:37:25.994 --> 00:37:27.912
I believe you.

333
00:37:27.996 --> 00:37:30.248
And the police-

334
00:37:30.331 --> 00:37:32.292
They were here?

335
00:37:33.793 --> 00:37:37.088
- You told 'em nothing, right?
- Right.

336
00:37:37.172 --> 00:37:40.008
<i>Of course.</i>

337
00:37:41.092 --> 00:37:43.720
You couldn't talk.

338
00:37:43.803 --> 00:37:45.680
Yeah.

339
00:37:49.934 --> 00:37:51.895
Let's keep it that way.

340
00:37:51.978 --> 00:37:54.397
[Groaning]

341
00:37:58.568 --> 00:38:01.237
<i>[Rapid Beeping]</i>

342
00:38:03.948 --> 00:38:05.909
<i>[Steady Beep]</i>

343
00:38:11.289 --> 00:38:14.709
<i>[Alarm Beeping]</i>

344
00:38:14.793 --> 00:38:17.295
<i>- [Alarm Stops]
- [Rhythmic Beeping]</i>

345
00:38:41.277 --> 00:38:43.446
♪♪ [Humming Softly]

346
00:38:48.034 --> 00:38:49.953
♪♪ [Stops}

347
00:38:51.204 --> 00:38:53.873
I picked them
from the garden outside.

348
00:38:53.957 --> 00:38:56.668
I hope you don't mind.

349
00:38:56.751 --> 00:38:59.671
I didn't know
if you liked coffee or tea...

350
00:38:59.754 --> 00:39:01.297
<i>so I made both.</i>

351
00:39:01.381 --> 00:39:04.050
<i>[Bell Dings]</i>

352
00:39:14.352 --> 00:39:17.021
I hope you like, uh...

353
00:39:17.105 --> 00:39:19.607
"madeleines."

354
00:39:19.691 --> 00:39:21.776
Try one.

355
00:39:24.737 --> 00:39:26.197
Careful.

356
00:39:26.281 --> 00:39:27.574
It's hot.

357
00:39:30.451 --> 00:39:31.953
Good?

358
00:39:37.959 --> 00:39:39.460
Let me.

359
00:39:41.004 --> 00:39:43.006
I like it quiet
in the morning.

360
00:39:43.089 --> 00:39:45.133
Yes. Quiet in the morning.

361
00:39:45.216 --> 00:39:47.802
Me too. Me too.
I'm the same way.

362
00:39:47.886 --> 00:39:50.305
I like very quiet.

363
00:39:52.432 --> 00:39:54.309
Sorry.

364
00:40:00.231 --> 00:40:01.816
Are you looking for milk?

365
00:40:03.276 --> 00:40:05.320
Ah, there's milk
at the door.

366
00:40:05.403 --> 00:40:07.697
Stay. Stay. I'll go.

367
00:40:17.707 --> 00:40:19.626
And you are?

368
00:40:19.709 --> 00:40:23.379
- The new cook.
- Is Monsieur Frank in?

369
00:40:23.463 --> 00:40:26.716
Ah. Monsieur Frank.

370
00:40:26.799 --> 00:40:29.093
Is your invitation
for coffee still open?

371
00:40:29.177 --> 00:40:31.095
- Sure. Come on. Please.
- Mm-hmm.

372
00:40:31.179 --> 00:40:33.181
Sit.

373
00:40:34.307 --> 00:40:36.225
- Madeleine?
- Homemade?

374
00:40:36.309 --> 00:40:39.437
<i>Yes. I'll bring some more.</i>

375
00:40:39.520 --> 00:40:43.900
Ah. My mother used to make
fresh madeleines every morning.

376
00:40:43.983 --> 00:40:48.279
I smell them, and my whole
childhood comes back in one big flood.

377
00:40:48.363 --> 00:40:51.741
Like Proust.
You ever read Proust, Monsieur Frank?

378
00:40:51.824 --> 00:40:53.326
- Nope.
- Ah.

379
00:40:53.409 --> 00:40:56.788
He's fantastic.
Memory like a steel trap.

380
00:40:56.871 --> 00:40:59.290
He would have been
a great cop. Real determined.

381
00:40:59.374 --> 00:41:01.000
- Milk?
- Please, milk.

382
00:41:02.710 --> 00:41:05.922
Thank you. Ah.

383
00:41:06.005 --> 00:41:08.508
<i>l used to have
a memory like Proust.</i>

384
00:41:08.591 --> 00:41:10.677
Like a ﬁling cabinet
up there.

385
00:41:10.760 --> 00:41:13.262
I would see something
and remember it like that.

386
00:41:13.346 --> 00:41:17.976
Like, uh, license plates. I could see a plate,
and it was printed in my head.

387
00:41:18.059 --> 00:41:20.228
Now l need
all the help I can get...

388
00:41:20.311 --> 00:41:23.314
remembering, uh,
whose plate goes with whose car.

389
00:41:23.398 --> 00:41:26.275
Like, uh, this one.

390
00:41:28.528 --> 00:41:30.780
- That's mine.
- Ah.

391
00:41:30.863 --> 00:41:33.157
- Memories.
- So?

392
00:41:33.241 --> 00:41:35.994
- Where's the rest of the car?
- I was hoping you could tell me.

393
00:41:36.077 --> 00:41:37.996
- It was stolen.
- Stolen?

394
00:41:38.079 --> 00:41:41.624
I went down to Fréjus to pick up a few things.
When I came out of the market, it was-

395
00:41:41.708 --> 00:41:43.710
Gone.

396
00:41:43.793 --> 00:41:46.879
- You report it?
- That's the first on my list of things to do today.

397
00:41:46.963 --> 00:41:49.882
It's a long walk from Fréjus.
How did you get home?

398
00:41:49.966 --> 00:41:51.926
<i>I brought him.</i>

399
00:41:53.761 --> 00:41:56.139
I saw him walking along
the dark road.

400
00:41:56.222 --> 00:42:00.727
A risky thing, picking up a stranger
on a dark road.

401
00:42:01.769 --> 00:42:03.730
He had a kind face.

402
00:42:07.191 --> 00:42:10.153
- I didn't see a car outside.
- It's in the garage.

403
00:42:10.236 --> 00:42:12.613
- May I see it?
- Mm-hmm.

404
00:42:27.378 --> 00:42:29.756
[Whistles]
Wow.

405
00:42:32.842 --> 00:42:35.595
Ah. Pretty nice car
for a cook.

406
00:42:37.764 --> 00:42:40.725
Some people have a problem
with the Germans.

407
00:42:40.808 --> 00:42:44.353
They are too aggressive.
They take up the best beaches in summer.

408
00:42:44.437 --> 00:42:46.439
They can't cook worth a damn.

409
00:42:49.525 --> 00:42:54.489
I say anyone makes
such great cars can't be all bad.

410
00:42:54.572 --> 00:42:58.951
I would say your intuition worked out very well
for Monsieur Frank, mademoiselle.

411
00:42:59.035 --> 00:43:01.496
Worked out for both of us.

412
00:43:06.167 --> 00:43:08.211
<i>Bon.</i> Uh-

413
00:43:08.294 --> 00:43:10.421
My intuition says
this is...

414
00:43:10.505 --> 00:43:12.965
probably a good time
for me to go file my report.

415
00:43:13.049 --> 00:43:15.885
- Where's the rest of my car?
<i>- Oh, yes.</i>

416
00:43:15.968 --> 00:43:19.847
I almost forgot.
It was blown to pieces at a rest stop.

417
00:43:21.140 --> 00:43:24.393
What's left of it
is down at the lab.

418
00:43:24.477 --> 00:43:28.689
They are trying to separate
what was left of the two cops in the trunk...

419
00:43:28.773 --> 00:43:31.067
from the rest of it.

420
00:43:31.150 --> 00:43:34.195
But, uh, you wouldn't know
anything about that.

421
00:43:34.278 --> 00:43:37.156
- No.
- Sorry to interrupt.

422
00:43:37.240 --> 00:43:39.826
Thank you for the coffee
and the memories.

423
00:43:39.909 --> 00:43:41.661
Come back anytime.

424
00:43:41.744 --> 00:43:45.498
- Would you mind walking me?
- No.

425
00:43:45.581 --> 00:43:49.127
You have always been very quiet
about your business, Monsieur Frank.

426
00:43:49.210 --> 00:43:52.171
I appreciate that.
Less work for mother.

427
00:43:52.255 --> 00:43:56.092
But this business at the rest stop.
That is not very quiet.

428
00:43:56.175 --> 00:44:00.638
I don't suppose you would like to tell me
something besides a stolen car story?

429
00:44:00.721 --> 00:44:03.724
- If I had one, I would.
- Well, may I suggest...

430
00:44:03.808 --> 00:44:06.769
that when the two of you
show up in my office after lunch...

431
00:44:06.853 --> 00:44:08.771
you do have one.

432
00:44:08.855 --> 00:44:11.065
A better one
than you currently have.

433
00:44:18.030 --> 00:44:20.283
You are the one
he wants to see...

434
00:44:20.366 --> 00:44:22.827
- not me.
- Quiet!

435
00:44:22.910 --> 00:44:24.996
Please. I have to think.

436
00:44:25.079 --> 00:44:26.998
You were supposed
to think last night.

437
00:44:27.081 --> 00:44:29.667
Yeah, well, last night
I had nightmares...

438
00:44:29.750 --> 00:44:34.213
about a girl who came into my nice, quiet life,
screwed it all up.

439
00:44:34.297 --> 00:44:37.383
Everything she touched broke, and every move
she made turned into a catastrophe.

440
00:44:37.466 --> 00:44:39.760
Okay. Sorry.

441
00:44:42.054 --> 00:44:46.767
I'm still wondering if I want to know
everything or nothing about you.

442
00:44:54.901 --> 00:44:56.861
What?

443
00:44:56.944 --> 00:45:00.615
- It's the quiet.
- I thought you like quiet.

444
00:45:00.698 --> 00:45:03.534
<i>[Insect Buzzes]</i>

445
00:45:03.618 --> 00:45:06.454
Yeah. Not this quiet.

446
00:45:09.707 --> 00:45:11.250
[Screams]

447
00:45:22.929 --> 00:45:25.514
[Coughing]

448
00:45:25.598 --> 00:45:27.558
- You okay?
- No.

449
00:45:27.642 --> 00:45:29.602
Good. Let's go.

450
00:45:37.985 --> 00:45:39.362
[Shouting]

451
00:45:39.445 --> 00:45:40.780
Go, go, go!

452
00:45:46.786 --> 00:45:48.329
[Grunts]

453
00:45:51.624 --> 00:45:52.875
- [Groans]
- [Yelps]

454
00:45:53.793 --> 00:45:56.128
No. Don't stay there!

455
00:45:57.964 --> 00:45:59.507
[Screams]

456
00:46:04.595 --> 00:46:06.597
[Screams]

457
00:46:06.681 --> 00:46:08.641
[Gasping]

458
00:46:08.724 --> 00:46:10.893
<i>[Metal Clangs]</i>

459
00:46:23.864 --> 00:46:25.199
Frank!

460
00:46:27.660 --> 00:46:29.328
Come on. Give me your hand.

461
00:46:32.498 --> 00:46:33.833
[Screams]

462
00:46:35.293 --> 00:46:36.502
<i>[Lai Screams]</i>

463
00:46:40.840 --> 00:46:42.550
[Grunts]

464
00:46:51.892 --> 00:46:54.228
- [Screaming]
- Come on.

465
00:46:56.397 --> 00:46:57.940
Come on. Get in. Get in!

466
00:46:58.024 --> 00:46:59.942
- No! No!
- Get in!

467
00:47:03.029 --> 00:47:05.823
Lai, look! Come on.
Do you want to die?

468
00:47:05.906 --> 00:47:07.241
Get in!

469
00:47:08.534 --> 00:47:10.536
[Shouts]

470
00:47:11.579 --> 00:47:13.456
[Screams]

471
00:47:26.886 --> 00:47:28.888
[Gasping]

472
00:47:30.264 --> 00:47:32.308
- Calm down. Okay?
- [Sobbing]

473
00:47:32.391 --> 00:47:34.727
Don't worry.
You okay?

474
00:47:34.810 --> 00:47:37.521
- Stay here. I'm comin' back.
- No.

475
00:47:37.605 --> 00:47:39.565
Wait! Wait!

476
00:47:49.492 --> 00:47:51.494
[Screams]

477
00:47:52.953 --> 00:47:55.456
Put it on.

478
00:47:56.499 --> 00:47:58.417
- You okay?
- Mmm.

479
00:47:58.501 --> 00:48:00.795
Sure? Okay. Let's go.

480
00:49:40.811 --> 00:49:42.980
Frank.

481
00:49:43.063 --> 00:49:44.815
<i>Is this your house?</i>

482
00:49:44.899 --> 00:49:46.442
<i>- [Electricity Crackling]</i>
- [Gasps]

483
00:49:48.235 --> 00:49:51.614
<i>- Frank.</i>
- [Grunts] Yeah. Guess.

484
00:49:54.366 --> 00:49:56.577
Frank.

485
00:50:03.167 --> 00:50:05.586
Should mind my own
goddamn business.

486
00:50:07.505 --> 00:50:10.966
Simple rule.
Simple little rule.

487
00:50:11.050 --> 00:50:14.053
There's gotta be
some dry clothes in this house.

488
00:50:15.471 --> 00:50:18.182
Don't open the package.

489
00:50:18.265 --> 00:50:20.976
Nothin' but trouble
you open the goddamn package.

490
00:50:22.061 --> 00:50:23.979
<i>Frank.</i>

491
00:50:28.442 --> 00:50:31.278
- What are you doing?
- Making up for the trouble.

492
00:50:37.576 --> 00:50:41.288
- Wait. Wait. Why are you making-
- No more questions.

493
00:50:43.624 --> 00:50:46.877
Wait. I don't like it
when things get complicated.

494
00:50:46.961 --> 00:50:49.463
You like things simple.

495
00:50:49.547 --> 00:50:51.549
Very simple.

496
00:51:07.398 --> 00:51:10.693
<i>I'm not so clear about the house.
Could you explain?</i>

497
00:51:11.694 --> 00:51:14.029
Mmm. One more time.
After I left-

498
00:51:14.113 --> 00:51:16.740
After you left, we went for a walk
on the beach, had a swim.

499
00:51:16.824 --> 00:51:18.742
<i>- Where again?</i>
- Past the point.

500
00:51:18.826 --> 00:51:21.579
- Anyone else swimming at that time?
- No.

501
00:51:21.662 --> 00:51:24.456
- Did you see anybody else swimming?
- No. No one.

502
00:51:24.540 --> 00:51:28.168
So, you took a walk...

503
00:51:28.252 --> 00:51:31.880
had a swim... on a beach where
no one else was swimming...

504
00:51:31.964 --> 00:51:37.094
past the point, where you can't see or be seen
from the beach on either side...

505
00:51:37.177 --> 00:51:39.763
which makes witnesses
a little hard to come by.

506
00:51:39.847 --> 00:51:42.433
<i>That's the point
of a romantic swim.</i>

507
00:51:42.516 --> 00:51:44.685
Who wants witnesses?

508
00:51:46.812 --> 00:51:50.524
- And then?
- Then we came back to the house,
found it on ﬁre.

509
00:51:50.608 --> 00:51:53.902
-Just like that? On ﬁre?
- Yes.

510
00:51:53.986 --> 00:51:58.949
And the 5,000 rounds of spent ammo
my men found all around the house?

511
00:51:59.033 --> 00:52:01.994
- Maybe they had the wrong house.
- Monsieur Frank...

512
00:52:02.077 --> 00:52:04.872
people with
this kind of firepower…

513
00:52:04.955 --> 00:52:07.916
do not make mistakes
about who they visit.

514
00:52:09.168 --> 00:52:10.878
Who would want you
this dead?

515
00:52:10.961 --> 00:52:12.713
I don't know.

516
00:52:12.796 --> 00:52:15.841
- Any problems with a client?
- I don't have clients.

517
00:52:15.924 --> 00:52:18.927
I'm retired. I live on my army pension.
You know that.

518
00:52:19.011 --> 00:52:22.598
<i>You have all the facts of who I am
and who I was. You've had them for years.</i>

519
00:52:22.681 --> 00:52:25.476
Any enemies you can think of?
People from the past?

520
00:52:25.559 --> 00:52:27.603
I left the past behind
when I moved here.

521
00:52:27.686 --> 00:52:30.439
Hmm. A past like yours...

522
00:52:30.522 --> 00:52:32.691
-you never leave behind.
<i>- [Knocks]</i>

523
00:52:32.775 --> 00:52:35.444
[Speaking French]

524
00:52:35.527 --> 00:52:39.239
I'll just be a moment.
Don't leave.

525
00:52:53.629 --> 00:52:57.883
- What are you doin'?
- Computers know everything.
You just need a password.

526
00:52:57.966 --> 00:53:00.260
What are you, nuts?
We're in a police station.

527
00:53:00.344 --> 00:53:04.973
<i>You're always complaining. Except when
we make love. Then you say nothing.</i>

528
00:53:18.445 --> 00:53:19.947
- Uh-huh.
- [Beeps]

529
00:53:20.656 --> 00:53:23.242
<i>Ah.</i>

530
00:53:28.789 --> 00:53:31.959
<i>La, la, la.
Hello.</i>

531
00:53:32.042 --> 00:53:33.585
See?

532
00:53:40.467 --> 00:53:42.010
<i>[Computer Beeping]</i>

533
00:53:42.094 --> 00:53:43.971
<i>[Beeping Stops]</i>

534
00:53:52.146 --> 00:53:55.065
- So, where will you be staying?
- I don't know.

535
00:53:55.149 --> 00:53:57.860
Well, my cousin has
a small hotel.

536
00:53:58.944 --> 00:54:01.113
Thanks, but we'll manage.

537
00:54:01.196 --> 00:54:04.199
Without money,
could be hard.

538
00:54:04.283 --> 00:54:07.578
Here. It's not much, but at least
you won't go hungry.

539
00:54:07.661 --> 00:54:09.997
Thank you.

540
00:54:21.925 --> 00:54:24.303
- Where you goin'?
- Going to see that guy.

541
00:54:24.386 --> 00:54:26.847
- Good luck.
- One moment.

542
00:54:26.930 --> 00:54:29.767
- You're not coming?
- No.

543
00:54:29.850 --> 00:54:32.853
- But he blew up your car.
- I'll buy a new one.

544
00:54:32.936 --> 00:54:35.355
- He burned your house.
- I'll rebuild it.

545
00:54:35.439 --> 00:54:38.275
- He tried to kill you.
- And as far as he knows, he succeeded.

546
00:54:38.358 --> 00:54:40.277
Look. I'm gonna give you
some advice.

547
00:54:40.360 --> 00:54:42.863
I don't know what you're into.
I don't care what you're into.

548
00:54:42.946 --> 00:54:46.283
But whoever wanted you dead thinks
you're dead. You have a free pass to start over.

549
00:54:46.366 --> 00:54:48.869
Here's the advice:
Start over.

550
00:54:54.833 --> 00:54:57.544
There are 400 people...

551
00:54:57.628 --> 00:55:01.340
dying in a container
on a ship.

552
00:55:04.051 --> 00:55:06.553
My father.

553
00:55:06.637 --> 00:55:09.056
My sisters.

554
00:55:09.139 --> 00:55:11.809
The ship arrives today.

555
00:55:11.892 --> 00:55:15.103
<i>They will make
my father a slave.</i>

556
00:55:15.187 --> 00:55:19.316
The only one who knows
the container number...

557
00:55:19.399 --> 00:55:21.819
is that guy.

558
00:55:21.902 --> 00:55:23.737
You're very good.

559
00:55:23.821 --> 00:55:25.864
What do you mean?

560
00:55:25.948 --> 00:55:28.283
From the moment you saw
those pictures in my house...

561
00:55:28.367 --> 00:55:30.536
you were setting me up
to get involved in this.

562
00:55:30.619 --> 00:55:34.790
Breakfast. Giving the excuse to the cop
to help me. One lie after another.

563
00:55:36.625 --> 00:55:38.627
Not everything is a lie.

564
00:55:38.710 --> 00:55:41.046
Name one thing that isn't.

565
00:55:43.799 --> 00:55:46.009
What happened in the house...

566
00:55:46.093 --> 00:55:48.053
between us.

567
00:55:48.136 --> 00:55:50.639
That was not a lie.

568
00:55:53.433 --> 00:55:55.394
You were a soldier.

569
00:55:55.477 --> 00:55:58.272
Your job was to save people.

570
00:55:58.355 --> 00:56:01.191
- Past tense.
- What does that mean?

571
00:56:01.275 --> 00:56:03.443
Means I got tired of
seeing my best efforts...

572
00:56:03.527 --> 00:56:07.072
get turned into bullshit by the same people
who pay me to do the job.

573
00:56:07.155 --> 00:56:10.033
- No one cared.
- This time...

574
00:56:10.117 --> 00:56:12.077
I care.

575
00:56:27.092 --> 00:56:29.386
[Chuckles]
Thank you.

576
00:56:35.893 --> 00:56:37.811
<i>[Phone Rings]</i>

577
00:56:39.855 --> 00:56:41.982
<i>- Bonjour.
- Bonjour.</i>

578
00:56:42.065 --> 00:56:44.651
No phone calls
for half an hour?

579
00:56:44.735 --> 00:56:46.528
<i>Hello. Surprise.</i>

580
00:56:46.612 --> 00:56:48.488
[Groans]

581
00:56:53.911 --> 00:56:55.913
Sit.

582
00:57:07.257 --> 00:57:09.593
Put your hands
where I can see 'em.

583
00:57:09.676 --> 00:57:12.137
<i>So, before we get to
the heart of the matter…</i>

584
00:57:12.220 --> 00:57:14.139
<i>I have one question for you.</i>

585
00:57:14.222 --> 00:57:16.850
- Why'd you try to kill me?
- You lied to me.

586
00:57:16.934 --> 00:57:20.938
You opened the package.
You broke the rules. Your rules.

587
00:57:21.021 --> 00:57:24.191
What'd you expect me to do?
Recommend you for another job?

588
00:57:27.736 --> 00:57:29.488
What's the ship number?

589
00:57:32.366 --> 00:57:35.452
Mr. Transporter,
we can both agree.

590
00:57:35.535 --> 00:57:37.621
I answered your first
question politely.

591
00:57:37.704 --> 00:57:39.623
I won't answer any more.

592
00:57:39.706 --> 00:57:42.834
So I suggest
you kill me right now...

593
00:57:43.669 --> 00:57:46.380
and go screw yourself.

594
00:57:48.507 --> 00:57:50.509
I can't find anything.

595
00:57:56.848 --> 00:57:59.142
<i>Oh, poor Frank.</i>

596
00:57:59.226 --> 00:58:03.021
What'd she tell you? We're smuggling
people in containers? I tell you.

597
00:58:03.105 --> 00:58:05.232
- Lai's the perfect name for her.
<i>- [Phone Beeps]</i>

598
00:58:05.315 --> 00:58:06.733
Mr. Kwai's on the way up.

599
00:58:06.817 --> 00:58:09.778
Your father's here.
He'll really get a kick out of this.

600
00:58:09.861 --> 00:58:13.490
- I thought your father was in a container.
-Yes. I-I mean, no.

601
00:58:13.573 --> 00:58:17.077
<i>There are 400 people
in that container.</i>

602
00:58:17.160 --> 00:58:18.870
Stay where you are.

603
00:58:18.954 --> 00:58:22.040
She's a real heartbreaker,
isn't she, Frank?

604
00:58:23.709 --> 00:58:25.752
Ten seconds, two choices.

605
00:58:25.836 --> 00:58:29.548
The information on the paper or your brains
on the desk. Now tell me I'm lying.

606
00:58:29.631 --> 00:58:31.925
- Nine, eight-
<i>- Lai. Lai.</i>

607
00:58:32.009 --> 00:58:34.553
- Give me the gun.
- I don't know what you're talking about.

608
00:58:34.636 --> 00:58:36.847
…five, four...

609
00:58:36.930 --> 00:58:38.682
three, two-

610
00:58:38.765 --> 00:58:41.393
One. Shoot.

611
00:58:43.645 --> 00:58:46.023
<i>- [Door Opens]</i>
- Lai.

612
00:58:46.106 --> 00:58:50.402
[Speaking Chinese]

613
00:58:53.697 --> 00:58:57.534
- [Chinese]
- Would I kill my own daughter?

614
00:58:57.617 --> 00:58:59.619
Lai.

615
00:59:00.620 --> 00:59:02.622
Come on now.

616
00:59:02.706 --> 00:59:04.624
Put it down.

617
00:59:06.668 --> 00:59:09.504
We'll talk.

618
00:59:10.797 --> 00:59:13.425
She thinks we're smuggling
people in containers.

619
00:59:14.968 --> 00:59:17.429
- I don't know where you get these ideas.
- Stay away!

620
00:59:21.933 --> 00:59:24.686
Would you kill
your own father?

621
00:59:24.770 --> 00:59:27.773
Please. I'm begging you.

622
00:59:27.856 --> 00:59:29.816
Stop what you are doing.

623
00:59:29.900 --> 00:59:33.028
I do what I do.
I am who I am.

624
00:59:33.111 --> 00:59:35.822
I'll never change.
So, if you're going to kill me...

625
00:59:35.906 --> 00:59:37.908
kill me.

626
00:59:37.991 --> 00:59:39.993
<i>But if you don't…</i>

627
00:59:40.077 --> 00:59:42.496
get this gun out of my face.

628
00:59:45.207 --> 00:59:46.875
Give me.

629
00:59:46.958 --> 00:59:48.335
No!
[Chinese]

630
00:59:48.418 --> 00:59:51.755
I know he's innocent.
Oh, you have such a good heart.

631
00:59:51.838 --> 00:59:55.008
<i>Always interested
in saving innocent people.</i>

632
00:59:55.092 --> 00:59:57.969
Well, here's your big chance.
Drop your gun...

633
00:59:58.053 --> 01:00:00.639
<i>and you will save one.</i>

634
01:00:02.974 --> 01:00:04.976
[Chuckles]

635
01:00:06.019 --> 01:00:08.146
- Kill him!
- No!

636
01:00:08.230 --> 01:00:10.607
<i>[Phone Rings]</i>

637
01:00:10.690 --> 01:00:12.734
- The police are on their way up.
- What now?

638
01:00:12.818 --> 01:00:15.237
Take her.

639
01:00:15.320 --> 01:00:19.032
- [Beeps]
- Send in Leo. I need him to wrap something up.

640
01:00:35.257 --> 01:00:38.635
Just for the record,
there are 400 people in that container.

641
01:00:38.718 --> 01:00:42.639
Only 395 made it
here alive.

642
01:00:42.722 --> 01:00:44.432
Frank!

643
01:00:47.853 --> 01:00:52.232
- Inspector. Am I glad you're here.
- What is this?

644
01:00:52.315 --> 01:00:55.735
This man used my partner's daughter here
to try and blackmail us.

645
01:00:55.819 --> 01:00:58.446
Luckily, my security
got the drop on him.

646
01:00:58.530 --> 01:01:02.659
<i>l wanna press charges-
kidnapping, extortion, assault.</i>

647
01:01:02.742 --> 01:01:05.662
- I know this man.
- Well, I suppose in your business...

648
01:01:05.745 --> 01:01:08.081
you have to know all types.

649
01:01:10.167 --> 01:01:12.085
Now, should
I call my lawyer?

650
01:01:12.169 --> 01:01:14.379
We'll handle it.

651
01:01:19.176 --> 01:01:22.429
I'll expect all of you down at my office
to give your statements.

652
01:01:22.512 --> 01:01:26.474
As soon as I contact my lawyer,
we'll be more than happy to oblige.

653
01:01:34.441 --> 01:01:36.610
[Groans]

654
01:01:46.119 --> 01:01:49.873
<i>The doctor said you will have a headache
fora few days, and then everything…</i>

655
01:01:49.956 --> 01:01:51.875
<i>- will go back to normal</i>
- Where are they?

656
01:01:51.958 --> 01:01:54.544
I think you should
be more concerned...

657
01:01:54.628 --> 01:01:56.963
with where you are.

658
01:01:58.590 --> 01:02:00.550
What got into you?

659
01:02:00.634 --> 01:02:03.637
- You were always so careful.
- I've got to get out of here.

660
01:02:03.720 --> 01:02:06.056
Oh, well, with
the charges they ﬁled...

661
01:02:06.139 --> 01:02:09.017
you will not be getting out
for a very long time.

662
01:02:09.100 --> 01:02:11.478
<i>Assaulting
a distinguished member…</i>

663
01:02:11.561 --> 01:02:14.064
of the international
business community...

664
01:02:14.147 --> 01:02:16.524
kidnapping his daughter,
extortion.

665
01:02:16.608 --> 01:02:19.569
<i>- [Cell Door Closes]</i>
- I'm sorry, Frank.

666
01:02:19.653 --> 01:02:21.655
I would like
to help you...

667
01:02:21.738 --> 01:02:24.241
but if you continue
with the same old story...

668
01:02:24.324 --> 01:02:26.826
"I'm retired,
living on a pension"-

669
01:02:28.203 --> 01:02:30.205
<i>I need fresh, Frank.</i>

670
01:02:30.288 --> 01:02:31.831
I need new.

671
01:02:31.915 --> 01:02:34.167
For once,
I need the truth.

672
01:02:37.128 --> 01:02:39.256
Okay.

673
01:02:39.339 --> 01:02:41.466
They're smuggling people...

674
01:02:41.549 --> 01:02:44.344
from Asia through Marseille
in containers.

675
01:02:46.846 --> 01:02:50.016
- You know this for fact?
- The girl told me.

676
01:02:50.100 --> 01:02:52.852
- You believe her?
- Yes.

677
01:02:52.936 --> 01:02:55.480
In French we have a saying,
"Never believe the cook."

678
01:02:57.899 --> 01:03:00.527
- She's not the cook.
- Oh.

679
01:03:00.610 --> 01:03:02.779
I suspected.

680
01:03:02.862 --> 01:03:05.156
You know, Frank,
no one is perfect.

681
01:03:05.240 --> 01:03:08.159
- So you're saying you're gonna do nothing?
- No, I'm saying...

682
01:03:08.243 --> 01:03:10.245
I'm going to start
an investigation.

683
01:03:10.328 --> 01:03:13.581
And in the meantime, the 400 people
in the container could be dead already.

684
01:03:13.665 --> 01:03:15.625
But what am I
supposed to do?

685
01:03:15.709 --> 01:03:18.128
- There are laws.
- Did it ever occur to you that sometimes...

686
01:03:18.211 --> 01:03:20.130
- you have to make your own law?
- Like you do?

687
01:03:20.213 --> 01:03:22.716
At least with me, it doesn't take 12 months
to get the job done.

688
01:03:22.799 --> 01:03:26.553
Oh, yes, I know.
That's what I admire about you, Frank.

689
01:03:26.636 --> 01:03:30.598
All that army training,
all that sneaking around-

690
01:03:30.682 --> 01:03:34.269
A man like you could probably
resolve this case in, how long?

691
01:03:34.352 --> 01:03:37.731
- Twelve hours?
- Less.

692
01:03:37.814 --> 01:03:41.151
Less?
Impressive.

693
01:03:41.234 --> 01:03:43.445
You would be the perfect man
for the job.

694
01:03:43.528 --> 01:03:46.114
Yes, if I were out.

695
01:03:46.197 --> 01:03:48.908
Yes, if you were out.

696
01:04:09.596 --> 01:04:11.556
Anybody moves
and I kill him.

697
01:04:11.639 --> 01:04:14.100
[Speaking French]

698
01:04:24.402 --> 01:04:27.155
<i>♪♪ [Woman Singing Pop]</i>

699
01:04:35.872 --> 01:04:38.458
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

700
01:04:46.383 --> 01:04:48.385
<i>♪♪ [Ends]</i>

701
01:04:48.468 --> 01:04:53.223
If this is how you transport,
I'm amazed you get any work at all.

702
01:04:53.306 --> 01:04:55.308
Come on.
Give me a hand.

703
01:05:03.858 --> 01:05:05.860
Maybe I should
go with you?

704
01:05:07.278 --> 01:05:10.031
Thanks, but, uh,
I'm better alone.

705
01:05:10.115 --> 01:05:13.201
That is a very small boat
to fight a very big war.

706
01:05:13.284 --> 01:05:16.329
Yep.
But it's a good boat.

707
01:05:16.413 --> 01:05:21.167
<i>Frank, here.
You'll need it.</i>

708
01:05:24.504 --> 01:05:26.673
Or maybe not.

709
01:06:02.250 --> 01:06:06.337
<i>[Beeping]</i>

710
01:06:06.421 --> 01:06:09.382
[Beeping Continues]

711
01:06:54.219 --> 01:06:57.096
The shipment's cleared.
Here's the paperwork.

712
01:06:57.180 --> 01:07:00.141
Take the highway all the way
to the first exit- Lyon.

713
01:07:00.225 --> 01:07:04.562
Go straight to the warehouse.
We'll be right behind you just in case.

714
01:07:20.787 --> 01:07:24.624
- Lai, we are ready to go.
- [Speaks Chinese]

715
01:07:29.462 --> 01:07:31.631
Lai, dear.

716
01:07:31.714 --> 01:07:35.134
<i>[Lai Speaking Chinese]</i>

717
01:07:36.135 --> 01:07:38.805
[Continues In Chinese]

718
01:07:38.888 --> 01:07:42.892
I spent thousands of dollars
for you to go to school and learn English.

719
01:07:42.976 --> 01:07:46.437
- The least you can do is speak it.
- I hate you.

720
01:07:50.733 --> 01:07:53.027
I'm still your father.

721
01:07:54.404 --> 01:07:56.406
Get her out of here!

722
01:08:12.880 --> 01:08:14.549
[Groans]

723
01:08:15.425 --> 01:08:17.552
Give me a minute.

724
01:08:17.635 --> 01:08:19.637
[Groans]

725
01:08:23.725 --> 01:08:25.685
[Groans]

726
01:08:44.746 --> 01:08:47.040
Keep him alive.

727
01:09:27.413 --> 01:09:29.415
[Engine Starts]

728
01:09:29.499 --> 01:09:31.709
Let's go!

729
01:10:24.470 --> 01:10:26.097
[Tires Screech]

730
01:10:27.724 --> 01:10:29.475
No, don't!

731
01:10:31.853 --> 01:10:34.480
Let's go!

732
01:10:55.835 --> 01:10:57.503
[Groans]

733
01:12:08.157 --> 01:12:09.742
[Groans]

734
01:12:59.584 --> 01:13:01.460
[Groaning]

735
01:13:03.713 --> 01:13:05.882
[Grunting]

736
01:14:01.395 --> 01:14:03.481
- [Chuckles]
- [Groans]

737
01:16:11.692 --> 01:16:13.694
[Groans]

738
01:16:20.576 --> 01:16:22.495
<i>♪♪ [Hip Hop]</i>

739
01:17:00.116 --> 01:17:02.368
[Grunts]

740
01:17:03.536 --> 01:17:05.538
<i>[Airplane Approaches]</i>

741
01:17:46.287 --> 01:17:48.205
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

742
01:17:48.289 --> 01:17:51.917
[Coughs]
I'm looking to do a little sightseeing.

743
01:17:52.001 --> 01:17:55.087
- This plane is not for tourists.
- [Chuckles]

744
01:17:56.755 --> 01:17:59.633
I'm not a tourist.

745
01:18:22.114 --> 01:18:25.367
- Call this guy and tell him to meet me.
- Sure.

746
01:18:25.451 --> 01:18:27.828
Where?

747
01:18:27.912 --> 01:18:29.914
Down there.

748
01:18:57.858 --> 01:18:59.610
Here!

749
01:19:05.658 --> 01:19:07.284
Careful!

750
01:19:25.678 --> 01:19:27.346
[Groans]

751
01:19:42.778 --> 01:19:44.530
<i>[Tires Squealing]</i>

752
01:19:46.407 --> 01:19:48.742
[Screams]

753
01:19:51.203 --> 01:19:53.205
Move up.

754
01:20:15.811 --> 01:20:17.104
Now.

755
01:20:41.170 --> 01:20:43.714
[Groans]

756
01:21:09.573 --> 01:21:10.949
[Groans]

757
01:21:57.538 --> 01:21:59.832
[Horn Honks]

758
01:22:08.257 --> 01:22:09.883
Get closer!

759
01:22:15.013 --> 01:22:17.141
- Steady!
- No, Dad, stop!

760
01:22:20.144 --> 01:22:22.980
- [Speaking Chinese]
<i>- Get away!</i>

761
01:22:37.119 --> 01:22:38.203
[Groans]

762
01:23:02.060 --> 01:23:05.105
[Groaning]

763
01:23:07.357 --> 01:23:10.235
[Groaning Continues]

764
01:23:48.857 --> 01:23:50.859
[Kwai]
Down!

765
01:24:01.370 --> 01:24:03.872
Hands on your head.

766
01:24:03.956 --> 01:24:05.958
Move!

767
01:24:07.793 --> 01:24:12.089
Watch her. If she moves or
I don't return, shoot her!

768
01:24:14.633 --> 01:24:16.552
To the water.

769
01:24:16.635 --> 01:24:19.471
- I'm really not in the mood for a swim.
- March!

770
01:24:22.266 --> 01:24:25.435
So, how did a lowlife like you
end up with my daughter?

771
01:24:25.519 --> 01:24:27.896
I found her in a bag.
Isn't that where you left her?

772
01:24:27.980 --> 01:24:30.482
You know nothing.
Move!

773
01:24:33.652 --> 01:24:37.197
You got involved with the wrong girl,
you dumb shit.

774
01:24:37.281 --> 01:24:39.783
<i>The delivery will
be made,</i>

775
01:24:39.866 --> 01:24:43.537
My daughter will get over it.
If I'm lucky, maybe she'll see the light.

776
01:24:49.376 --> 01:24:52.588
Yeah, if she's lucky,
maybe you'll get hit by a truck.

777
01:24:52.671 --> 01:24:56.258
- What do you know?
- I know she'll never stop being who she is...

778
01:24:56.341 --> 01:24:58.927
<i>and she'll never be you
or anything like you.</i>

779
01:24:59.011 --> 01:25:02.180
She'll come around,
but you won't be here to see it.

780
01:25:02.264 --> 01:25:04.933
<i>- [Lai] No!
- [Gunshot]</i>

781
01:25:13.775 --> 01:25:18.196
I guess she won't be
coming around after all.

782
01:25:19.698 --> 01:25:22.409
<i>- Turn around!</i>
- I'd rather see it coming.

783
01:25:22.492 --> 01:25:24.369
Makes no difference
to me.

784
01:25:26.622 --> 01:25:28.332
<i>[Gunshot]</i>

785
01:25:49.603 --> 01:25:52.189
He was a bastard...

786
01:25:52.272 --> 01:25:55.025
but he was still
my father.

787
01:26:05.160 --> 01:26:07.412
[Sniffles]

788
01:26:08.955 --> 01:26:10.957
<i>[Inspector]
Pretty impressive timing, Frank.</i>

789
01:26:14.628 --> 01:26:17.214
I guess
I underestimated you.

790
01:26:34.022 --> 01:26:36.566
[Speaking Chinese]

791
01:27:22.112 --> 01:27:25.031
<i>♪♪ [Mellow Rock]</i>

792
01:28:28.845 --> 01:28:31.848
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

793
01:30:19.539 --> 01:30:22.542
<i>♪♪ [Continues]</i>

794
01:31:59.180 --> 01:32:02.183
<i>♪♪ [Ends]</i>

